The possibility of counting the vote in Michoacán individually is taken into consideration
According to PREP, the difference between first and second place in the governor’s election is almost 27 percent, with 879 votes of a total of 6074 not yet counted.
The possibility of the individual count of the vote is a reality in the Michoacán elections this year, because according to the data issued by the Programmea de Resultados Electorale Preliminares (PREP), the difference between first and second place in the Governoral elections is almost 27 percent, with 879 votes of a total of 6074 not yet counted.
In this sense, the President of the Consejo General del Instituto Electoral de Michoacán (IEM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, reminded us that just last November, the electorate had adopted a number of arrangements on the benchmark of local regulations with the reforms of the States in electoral matters.
It should be remembered that Michoacán had adapted neither his political constitution nor his electoral law or law on electoral justice to the reforms adopted by Congress so that they had not entered into force during this round of elections.
On November 9th, the Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN) decided on the constitutional complaint submitted by the local legislature and voted the vote of the State Officer on the constitutional reforms as “unvaluable and unlawful, since it does not have the right to decide on it or to impose a veto against it.
María de los Ángeles Llanderal, in an interview on the possibility of individual counting of votes, explained that thanks to the adoption of the guidelines by the Consejo General del IEM, there was now the possibility that the local electoral authority could partially or completely count the vote.
Thus, under the following conditions, the votes contained in one or more electoral packages may be partially counted The results in the protocols do not agree; the protocol on voting and calculation is not currently available or it is not owned by the chairman of the electoral committee or there are obvious errors or amendments in the protocols.
In addition, the total count of the fully-filled ballots may take place if there is a difference between the alleged winner and the one in second place, which is equal or lower than one percent, provided that at the beginning of the session, there is an explicit request by the party or coalition chairman, who is the second of the candidates mentioned.
The voting bill may also take place in its entirety if, after completion of the proper calculation, it is determined that the difference between the alleged winner and the candidate in second place is equal to or less than one percent, provided there is an explicit application by a party representative whose candidate has become second. In this case, the electoral packages which have been exposed to a partial count would be excluded.
It is worth noting that the elections in Morelia are in the same situation, where according to PREP, the difference between first and second place is almost 0.16%, although the votes of 129 of a total of 923 electoral protocols have not yet been counted.
